<% content_for :page_title, "Home — Rails Stuffs" %>

<div class="page-hero">
  <h1>A small tour of Ruby on Rails</h1>
  <p class="lede">
    This app shows how routing, controllers, models, views, and the asset pipeline fit together in a typical Rails project.
  </p>
</div>

<div class="card-grid">
  <article class="card">
    <h2>About Rails</h2>
    <p>How MVC, REST, and convention over configuration shape a request.</p>
    <%= link_to "Read overview →", about_path, class: "card__link" %>
  </article>

  <article class="card">
    <h2>Dynamic page</h2>
    <p>Data from the controller appears in the view on each refresh.</p>
    <%= link_to "See server time →", demo_time_path, class: "card__link" %>
  </article>

  <article class="card">
    <h2>Articles (CRUD)</h2>
    <p>Active Record, strong parameters, forms, and redirects with flash.</p>
    <%= link_to "Open articles →", articles_path, class: "card__link" %>
  </article>
</div>
